@{
    Layout = "_Layout";
}
<style>
    .hero-economy {
        background: rgba(33, 37, 41, 0.85);
        color: #fff;
        padding: 3rem 1rem 2rem 1rem;
        border-radius: 16px;
        margin-top: 2rem;
        text-align: center;
        box-shadow: 0 4px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.15);
    }

    .economy-featured {
        background: #fff;
        border-radius: 16px;
        box-shadow: 0 4px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);
        padding: 2rem;
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    .economy-news-card {
        background: #fff;
        border-radius: 12px;
        box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
        padding: 1.2rem;
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        transition: box-shadow 0.2s;
    }

        .economy-news-card:hover {
            box-shadow: 0 6px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.12);
        }

    .economy-news-title {
        font-size: 1.15rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        color: #2d3a4a;
    }

    .economy-news-date {
        font-size: 0.95rem;
        color: #888;
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }
</style>

<!-- Hero Section -->
<section class="hero-economy container mt-4">
    <h1 class="display-5 fw-bold">Economy News</h1>
    <p class="lead">Stay updated with the latest trends, analysis, and headlines from the world of business and economics.</p>
</section>

<!-- Featured Economy News -->
<div class="container mt-4">
    <div class="economy-featured mb-4">
        <h3 class="mb-2">Global Markets Rally as Economic Data Beats Expectations</h3>
        <div class="economy-news-date">June 30, 2025</div>
        <p>
            Stock markets worldwide surged today after new economic data showed stronger-than-expected growth in major economies. Analysts predict continued momentum if positive trends persist.
        </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Economy News Grid -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="economy-news-card">
                <div class="economy-news-title">Central Banks Signal Interest Rate Pause</div>
                <div class="economy-news-date">June 29, 2025</div>
                <p>Major central banks hinted at a pause in interest rate hikes, citing easing inflation and stable job growth.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="economy-news-card">
                <div class="economy-news-title">Oil Prices Climb Amid Supply Concerns</div>
                <div class="economy-news-date">June 28, 2025</div>
                <p>Oil prices rose sharply as geopolitical tensions threatened supply routes, prompting renewed calls for energy diversification.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="economy-news-card">
                <div class="economy-news-title">Tech Sector Drives Job Creation</div>
                <div class="economy-news-date">June 27, 2025</div>
                <p>New data shows the technology sector continues to lead in job creation, boosting overall economic growth.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="economy-news-card">
                <div class="economy-news-title">Emerging Markets Attract Record Investments</div>
                <div class="economy-news-date">June 26, 2025</div>
                <p>Investors are pouring funds into emerging markets, drawn by strong growth prospects and favorable policies.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

